<font color="#FF0000">HOPE FOR ENDURANCE</font><br>
<tt>Fri Oct 17 22:29:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Art;<br>
You said a lot, we were but a small part in the big gamble, those that wage wars for pleasure had to encounter. <br><br>
For what it was worth we did stop those proud waves, checkmated their plans, hopes, and dreams for world dominion. The world recognizes this, but not our fellow Americans, who knows what else we prevented.<br><br>
Even the peace we shared with the South Vietnamese in the midst of chaos and war was more then what *communist peace* they had to survive under since our departure and those memories of our presence give them hope and reason to endure.<br><br>
Vietnam was as someone once before said, just another battle in the cold war against communism.<br>

